{
  "stem": "11290.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was really no way of breaking out of the-- of the existence, unless we, we did something that we were really not supposed to do.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So Munich was famous for its-- for its Fasching, which is the carnival, the Mardi Gras.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were wonderful balls in the big beer halls where everybody danced and had a great time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we used to go there once a year, or twice during that time to take part in it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in 1934, I decided that I was going to go with a mask and risk it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And actually, not that-- I didn't have a good time, personally.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I could watch the people walking up the stairs, down the stairs, the masses of people dancing and the music, and the whole atmosphere, which was really unique-- a total release of, of, of people's feelings for, for joy and freedom, and, and, and have fun.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I, I was recognized.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In spite of my mask, I was recognized by a former schoolmate, classmate of mine, who was, was a German, Aryan classmate.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he said to me, come with me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I show you-- [LAUGHS] I show you the leader of the SS and his boyfriends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there was Rohm sitting there on a big table with his-- with his friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was in January 1934.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And by the-- by June 1934, Rohm and a lot of these other SS leaders were shot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were killed by Hitler, under the pretense that they were homosexuals, which they actually were.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because there were only boys that he was sitting there in a very-- these balls are very heterosexual.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Everybody dances, and people kissed and embraced each other.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
